    "As Paczynski (1986) has shown, the κ, γ, κ * parameter space can be transformed to an equivalent, two-dimensional parameter space of effective convergence and shear:",
    "In the above equation, κ eff is entirely due to compact matter.",
    "The effect of the above transformation can be understood in the following way, as also illustrated in the top panel of Fig. 14.",
    "Starting from a given location κ 0, γ 0 with κ c = 0 (locations A and D), maps with κ c > 0 lie in the third dimension in the traditional κ, γ, κ * parameter space.",
    "But in the effective space they lie along straight lines defined by κ 0, γ 0 and (1, 0)."
